headline: Nvidia CEO Huang denies he is unhappy with OpenAI, says 'huge' investment planned

The chipmaker in September announced plans to invest up ‌to $100 billion in OpenAI, a deal that would give OpenAI the cash and access it needs to buy advanced ‌chips that are key to maintaining its dominance in an increasingly competitive landscape.  The Wall Street Journal reported on Friday that the plan had stalled after some inside the chip giant expressed doubts about the deal.
